item.description: I am a postdoctoral researcher in the Visual Geometry Group at the University of Oxford working with Prof. Andrea Vedaldi and Dr. Joao Henriques. My primary research interest is in self-supervised learning of visual representations for novel view synthesis and acquisition of 3D assets from raw in-the-wild data. I completed my PhD student at the Max Planck Institute for Informatics under the supervision of Prof. Bernt Schiele working on human pose estimation.
